Moi University is building partnerships with north
rift counties to help them in development programmes. Vice chancellor
Isaac Kosgey met Nandi Deputy Governor
Yulita Cheruiyot to discuss collaboration. "We are looking for opportunities to
work with Nandi to better service delivery‚Äù, the VC said. The deputy governor said experts from the
university could help tackle challenges facing Nandi farmers such as diseases
and pests. "Agriculture is our main economic pillar
in Nandi County and we will leverage on the expertise from Moi University to
